1. Best Free Option (Recommended)
BAAI/bge-large-en-v1.5

Why

Very strong semantic retrieval performance

Works extremely well for scientific literature

Open-source

Used widely in RAG systems

Specs

Property	Value
Dimension	1024
License	open
Strength	semantic retrieval
Hardware	GPU recommended

Example usage

from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer

model = SentenceTransformer("BAAI/bge-large-en-v1.5")

emb = model.encode(
    "machine learning for quantum parameter estimation",
    normalize_embeddings=True
)

This model often outperforms many API embeddings for search.

2. Lightweight Free Option
intfloat/e5-large-v2

Good alternative if you want something very stable.

Strengths:

trained for retrieval tasks

good for query ↔ document similarity

Usage pattern

query: machine learning for quantum metrology
passage: Neural-network Hamiltonian learning...

Example

model = SentenceTransformer("intfloat/e5-large-v2")
3. Smallest Good Model
bge-small-en-v1.5

Use if you want very fast inference.

Property	Value
Dimension	384
Speed	very fast
Quality	moderate

Good for:

large-scale pipelines

low GPU memory

4. API Free Tier (if you prefer API)
nvidia/llama-nemotron-embed-vl-1b-v2:free

Pros:

free tier

good multilingual embeddings

accessible via OpenRouter

Cons:

slightly weaker than BGE/E5 for retrieval.

Example

client.embeddings.create(
  model="nvidia/llama-nemotron-embed-vl-1b-v2:free",
  input=text
)
Recommended Choice for Your Pipeline

Since you're doing paper retrieval + semantic filtering, the best tradeoff is:

Use
BAAI/bge-large-en-v1.5

Reasons:

excellent semantic search

strong scientific text performance

free and open-source

widely used in research agents

Ideal Setup for Your Architecture
query_embedding = BGE(query)
paper_embedding = BGE(title + abstract)

similarity = cosine(query_embedding, paper_embedding)

Threshold:

0.65 – 0.75
If You Want the Absolute Best Free Setup

Use hybrid retrieval:

embedding search (BGE)
+
